OL,3,CSynod members to debate and vote on
OL,4,Cnew safeguarding model for Church of
OL,5,CEngland
OL,7,FA different option, known as model
OL,8,Fthree, would see most national staff
OL,9,Fmove to a new outside non-Church body,
OL,10,Fbut other diocesan and cathedral
OL,11,Fofficers remaining with their current
OL,12,FChurch employers.
OL,14,FBoth options would see safeguarding
OL,15,Fwork scrutinised by a second external
OL,16,Fbody, but papers published last month
OL,17,Fsay it would take "a minimum of two
OL,18,Fyears to legislate for a scrutiny body
OL,19,Fas a statutory body".
